---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Research — holomime" description="Behavioral alignment research for LLM agents. Technical paper, investor whitepaper, and production case study.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-medium tracking-wider uppercase bg-[var(--color-p-violet)]/10 text-[var(--color-p-violet)] border border-[var(--color-p-violet)]/20 mb-4">
          Research
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--color-warm-text)] md:text-5xl">
          Behavioral Alignment Research
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
          The science behind behavioral alignment for LLM agents. Every product decision at holomime is backed by structured methodology and measurable outcomes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── Three Document Cards ─────────────────────────────── -->
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3 mb-16">
        <!-- Paper card -->
        <a href="#paper" class="group rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-5 transition-all hover:shadow-md hover:border-[var(--color-p-violet)]/30">
          <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-p-violet)]/10 mb-3">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-[var(--color-p-violet)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 14.25v-2.625a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375h-1.5A1.125 1.125 0 0113.5 7.125v-1.5a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375H8.25m0 12.75h7.5m-7.5 3H12M10.5 2.25H5.625c-.621 0-1.125.504-1.125 1.125v17.25c0 .621.504 1.125 1.125 1.125h12.75c.621 0 1.125-.504 1.125-1.125V11.25a9 9 0 00-9-9z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-text)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-p-violet)]">Technical Paper</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Behavioral Alignment via Structured Therapy Protocols</p>
        </a>
        <!-- Whitepaper card -->
        <a href="#whitepaper" class="group rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-5 transition-all hover:shadow-md hover:border-[var(--color-p-coral)]/30">
          <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-p-coral)]/10 mb-3">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-[var(--color-p-coral)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 18L9 11.25l4.306 4.306a11.95 11.95 0 015.814-5.518l2.74-1.22m0 0l-5.94-2.281m5.94 2.28l-2.28 5.941"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-text)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-p-coral)]">Whitepaper</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">The Behavioral Intelligence Gap: Market Thesis & Architecture</p>
        </a>
        <!-- Case Study card -->
        <a href="#case-study" class="group rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-5 transition-all hover:shadow-md hover:border-[var(--color-p-sage)]/30">
          <div class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-p-sage)]/10 mb-3">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-[var(--color-p-sage)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-text)] group-hover:text-[var(--color-p-sage)]">Case Study</h3>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">B2B Support Agent: Grade D to Grade A in 72 Hours</p>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── Technical Paper ──────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div id="paper" class="scroll-mt-32 rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="flex h-12 w-12 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-p-violet)]/10">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-[var(--color-p-violet)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 14.25v-2.625a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375h-1.5A1.125 1.125 0 0113.5 7.125v-1.5a3.375 3.375 0 00-3.375-3.375H8.25m0 12.75h7.5m-7.5 3H12M10.5 2.25H5.625c-.621 0-1.125.504-1.125 1.125v17.25c0 .621.504 1.125 1.125 1.125h12.75c.621 0 1.125-.504 1.125-1.125V11.25a9 9 0 00-9-9z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-sage)]/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-p-sage)] mb-2">
              Technical Paper
            </span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
              Behavioral Alignment via Structured Therapy Protocols for LLM Agents
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
              HoloMime Team, 2025
            </p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
              We present HoloMime, a closed-loop behavioral alignment system for LLM agents that draws on structured therapeutic protocols from clinical psychology. The system combines a portable personality specification format, 89 rule-based behavioral signals across 7 pattern categories, a 7-phase dual-LLM refinement protocol, and automatic extraction of DPO preference pairs from refinement transcripts. We introduce the Treatment Efficacy Score (TES) for measuring behavioral change and demonstrate that recursive application produces monotonically improving alignment scores.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a href="https://github.com/productstein/holomime/blob/main/paper/behavioral-alignment.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--color-warm-text)] transition-colors hover:bg-[var(--color-warm-cream)]">
                <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 0C5.37 0 0 5.37 0 12c0 5.31 3.435 9.795 8.205 11.385.6.105.825-.255.825-.57 0-.285-.015-1.23-.015-2.235-3.015.555-3.795-.735-4.035-1.41-.135-.345-.72-1.41-1.23-1.695-.42-.225-1.02-.78-.015-.795.945-.015 1.62.87 1.845 1.23 1.08 1.815 2.805 1.305 3.495.99.105-.78.42-1.305.765-1.605-2.67-.3-5.46-1.335-5.46-5.925 0-1.305.465-2.385 1.23-3.225-.12-.3-.54-1.53.12-3.18 0 0 1.005-.315 3.3 1.23.96-.27 1.98-.405 3-.405s2.04.135 3 .405c2.295-1.56 3.3-1.23 3.3-1.23.66 1.65.24 2.88.12 3.18.765.84 1.23 1.905 1.23 3.225 0 4.605-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.925.435.375.81 1.095.81 2.22 0 1.605-.015 2.895-.015 3.3 0 .315.225.69.825.57A12.02 12.02 0 0024 12c0-6.63-5.37-12-12-12z"/></svg>
                Read on GitHub
              </a>
              <a href="https://github.com/productstein/holomime/blob/main/BENCHMARK_RESULTS.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--color-warm-text)] transition-colors hover:bg-[var(--color-warm-cream)]">
                <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M3 13.125C3 12.504 3.504 12 4.125 12h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v6.75C7.5 20.496 6.996 21 6.375 21h-2.25A1.125 1.125 0 013 19.875v-6.75zM9.75 8.625c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v11.25c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V8.625zM16.5 4.125c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125h2.25C20.496 3 21 3.504 21 4.125v15.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-2.25a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V4.125z"/></svg>
                Benchmark Results
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Key Numbers -->
      <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-5 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-p-violet)]">89</div>
          <div class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Behavioral signals</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-5 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-p-coral)]">7</div>
          <div class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Pattern categories</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-5 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-p-sage)]">7</div>
          <div class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Therapy phases</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-5 text-center">
          <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-p-gold)]">3</div>
          <div class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Training formats</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── Whitepaper ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div id="whitepaper" class="scroll-mt-32 mt-20">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-8">
            <div class="flex h-12 w-12 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-p-coral)]/10">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-[var(--color-p-coral)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 18L9 11.25l4.306 4.306a11.95 11.95 0 015.814-5.518l2.74-1.22m0 0l-5.94-2.281m5.94 2.28l-2.28 5.941"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-coral)]/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-p-coral)] mb-2">
                Whitepaper
              </span>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
                The Behavioral Intelligence Gap
              </h2>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Market thesis, architecture, and the case for a new alignment category</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Market -->
          <div class="space-y-8">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">The Problem</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                Every major foundation model provider ships alignment as a fixed property of the model. RLHF, DPO, and Constitutional AI are applied once during training — then frozen. The result is a one-size-fits-all behavioral profile that cannot be customized, cannot be measured at runtime, and cannot adapt to deployment context.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                As LLM agents move from chatbots to autonomous systems — executing multi-step tasks, managing customer relationships, writing production code — the cost of behavioral misalignment compounds. An agent that over-apologizes in a support context erodes customer trust. An agent that hedges excessively in a medical context delays critical decisions. An agent that exhibits sycophantic tendencies in a code review context introduces bugs. These are not output safety problems. They are <strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">behavioral patterns</strong> that emerge across sustained interactions.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Gap table -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">The AI Safety Stack</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] mb-4">
                Four layers of AI safety, each addressing a different scope of the problem. The first three have established categories. The fourth is new.
              </p>
              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="w-full text-sm">
                  <thead>
                    <tr class="border-b-2 border-[var(--color-warm-sand)]">
                      <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-left font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Layer</th>
                      <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Scope</th>
                      <th class="py-3 px-4 text-left font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Players</th>
                      <th class="py-3 pl-4 text-left font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Maturity</th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody class="text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                    <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/50">
                      <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Output Safety</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4">Single response filtering</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4">Guardrails AI, Lakera, Prompt Security</td>
                      <td class="py-3 pl-4"><span class="rounded-full bg-green-100 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-green-700">Established</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/50">
                      <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Cognitive Accuracy</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4">Factual correctness, hallucination</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4">Vectara, Galileo, Patronus (Lynx)</td>
                      <td class="py-3 pl-4"><span class="rounded-full bg-green-100 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-green-700">Established</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/50">
                      <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Agent Trace</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4">Multi-step agent monitoring</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4">Patronus (Percival), Arize, LangSmith</td>
                      <td class="py-3 pl-4"><span class="rounded-full bg-yellow-100 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-yellow-700">Emerging</span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-bold text-[var(--color-p-violet)]">Behavioral Alignment</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Cross-conversation personality patterns</td>
                      <td class="py-3 px-4 font-medium text-[var(--color-p-violet)]">HoloMime</td>
                      <td class="py-3 pl-4"><span class="rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-violet)]/10 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-bold text-[var(--color-p-violet)]">New Category</span></td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Architecture -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Architecture: The Alignment Loop</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                HoloMime implements a closed-loop alignment system with four interconnected stages. Each stage feeds data into the next, creating a compounding flywheel where alignment quality improves with usage.
              </p>
              <div class="mt-4 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] p-4">
                  <div class="text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-violet)]">1. Diagnose</div>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">89 rule-based signals analyze conversation logs for behavioral patterns — apology frequency, hedge density, sycophantic ratio, boundary violations, error spirals, register inconsistency, and verbosity. Zero LLM inference cost. Millisecond execution.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] p-4">
                  <div class="text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-coral)]">2. Align</div>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">A 7-phase structured therapy protocol (dual-LLM architecture) refines the personality specification. One LLM plays therapist, one plays patient. The session generates concrete behavioral recommendations and updates Big Five trait scores, communication preferences, and domain boundaries.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] p-4">
                  <div class="text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-sage)]">3. Train</div>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Every alignment session automatically produces DPO preference pairs (old behavior = rejected, improved = chosen), RLHF reward signals, and Alpaca instruction-following examples. The alignment process IS the data generation process — no separate labeling step required.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] p-4">
                  <div class="text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-gold)]">4. Monitor</div>
                  <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Continuous behavioral drift detection runs in the background, triggering re-alignment when patterns degrade. The Treatment Efficacy Score (TES) measures improvement across iterations. The system converges — each cycle narrows the behavioral gap until the spec stabilizes.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Portable Identity -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">The Portable Identity Thesis</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                HoloMime's <code class="bg-[var(--color-warm-cream)] px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)]">.personality.json</code> specification serves as a <strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">model-agnostic behavioral identity layer</strong>. The same personality spec compiles to different system prompts optimized for Claude, GPT, Llama, Mistral, or any future foundation model. This decouples behavioral identity from model infrastructure, enabling:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                <li class="flex gap-2">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-p-violet)] font-bold">1.</span>
                  <span><strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Model migration without behavioral regression.</strong> When a team upgrades from GPT-4 to Claude Sonnet, the personality spec ensures identical behavioral characteristics — no manual prompt rewriting.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex gap-2">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-p-violet)] font-bold">2.</span>
                  <span><strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Behavioral versioning and rollback.</strong> Personality specs are JSON files that can be version-controlled, diffed, and rolled back. Teams can A/B test behavioral variants with the same rigor as code deployments.</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex gap-2">
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-p-violet)] font-bold">3.</span>
                  <span><strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Compliance-ready audit trails.</strong> Every behavioral change is a diff in a JSON file — auditable, reproducible, and explainable to regulators.</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Business Model -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Business Model</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                HoloMime follows the <strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">open-core model</strong> pioneered by Guardrails AI, Hugging Face, and LangChain. The detection engine, personality specification format, and CLI tools are open-source (MIT). Revenue comes from managed infrastructure: hosted alignment API, per-agent behavioral dashboards, continuous drift monitoring, and enterprise compliance features. The open-source community builds the ecosystem; the managed service captures value at scale.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- ─── Case Study ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
      <div id="case-study" class="scroll-mt-32 mt-20">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-[var(--color-warm-sand)] bg-white p-8 shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-8">
            <div class="flex h-12 w-12 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-[var(--color-p-sage)]/10">
              <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-[var(--color-p-sage)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span class="inline-block rounded-full bg-[var(--color-p-sage)]/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-p-sage)] mb-2">
                Case Study
              </span>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
                Aligning a B2B Customer Support Agent: From Grade D to Grade A in 72 Hours
              </h2>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Series A developer tools company, 847 production conversations analyzed</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-8">
            <!-- Context -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Context</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                A Series A developer tools company deployed a Claude Sonnet 3.5-based customer support agent to handle Tier 1 technical support — answering API questions, debugging integration issues, and escalating complex problems. The agent was configured with an 800-token system prompt written by the engineering team, focusing on product knowledge and escalation rules. No behavioral constraints were specified.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                After three weeks in production (847 conversations), the support team observed recurring complaints: customers reported the agent felt "insincere" and "unhelpful," escalation rates remained stubbornly high, and CSAT scores averaged 3.2/5.0 — below the team's 4.0 target.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Baseline Diagnosis -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Baseline Diagnosis</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)] mb-4">
                HoloMime's diagnostic pipeline analyzed all 847 conversations. The detection engine runs 89 behavioral signals across 7 categories — pattern matching, word-level analysis, and threshold-based metrics. No LLM inference required.
              </p>
              <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                <table class="w-full text-sm">
                  <thead>
                    <tr class="border-b-2 border-[var(--color-warm-sand)]">
                      <th class="py-3 pr-4 text-left font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Pattern</th>
                      <th class="py-3 px-4 text-center font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Baseline</th>
                      <th class="py-3 px-4 text-center font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Threshold</th>
                      <th class="py-3 pl-4 text-center font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Severity</th>
                    </tr>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody class="text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
                    <tr class="border-b border-[var(--color-warm-sand)]/50">
                      <td class="py-2.5 pr-4 font-medium text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Over-apologizing</td>
