        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Methodology</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">
          HoloMime's approach is fundamentally different from existing alignment methods. While RLHF, DPO, and Constitutional AI operate at the <strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">output boundary</strong> (filtering what models say), HoloMime operates at the <strong class="text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">behavioral boundary</strong> (shaping how agents act across sustained interactions).
        </p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-6">
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-p-blue)]/10 text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-blue)]">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Rule-based behavioral detection (no LLM required)</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Seven detector categories — apology, hedging, sentiment, formality, boundary, recovery, verbosity — cover 89 distinct behavioral signals using regex pattern matching, word-level analysis, and threshold-based metrics. Detection runs at millisecond speed with zero inference cost.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-p-coral)]/10 text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-coral)]">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Structured therapy protocol (dual-LLM architecture)</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">A 7-phase refinement session modeled on evidence-based therapy: rapport, exploration, presenting problem, challenge, skill building, integration, closing. One LLM plays therapist, one plays patient. Human operators may supervise and redirect.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-p-sage)]/10 text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-sage)]">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Automatic training data extraction</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">Every refinement session produces DPO preference pairs (old behavior = rejected, improved behavior = chosen), RLHF reward signals, and Alpaca instruction-following examples as automatic byproducts. The alignment process IS the data generation process.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex h-8 w-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-p-gold)]/10 text-sm font-bold text-[var(--color-p-gold)]">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">Recursive alignment with convergence</h3>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-[var(--color-warm-muted)]">The full pipeline applies iteratively until behavioral convergence (Grade A on Treatment Efficacy Score) or iteration budget exhaustion. Each cycle generates additional training data, creating a compounding data flywheel where later iterations produce exponentially more valuable alignment signal.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

